---

<ProjectLayout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  keywords={pageKeywords}
  author={pageAuthor}
  applicationName={applicationName}
  url={pageUrl}
  image={pageImage}
  imageAlt={pageImageAlt}
  robots={pageRobots}
  canonical={pageCanonical}
  lang="en"
>
  <header class="text-center mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Interactive Advent Calendar</h1>
    <img
      transition:name={`img-${pageSlug}`}
      src={pageImage}
      alt={pageImageAlt}
      class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg mb-8"
    />
  </header>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl text-center font-semibold mb-4">
      ðŸŒŸ Challenge of the Week: December 4th to 10th ðŸŽ„
    </h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Theme: </strong>
      Create a digital advent calendar to celebrate the countdown to Christmas!
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Challenge Context: Alura Latam</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This project was born as part of a "Challenge of the Week" organized by the
      <a
        href="https://discord.gg/alumini-one"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Alumini ONE</a
      > group on Discord, a community of graduate students from the Oracle Next
      Education (ONE) program at Alura Latam.
    </p>
    <img
      src="/images/reto-calendario-adviento.jpg"
      alt="Screenshot of the Alumini ONE week challenge"
      class="mx-auto my-4 rounded-lg shadow-md"
    />
    <h3 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Recognition and Winners</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">
      I am pleased to share that this project was one of the winners of the December
      challenge! The official announcement from the Alumini ONE group confirmed it:
    </p>
    <img
      src="/images/ganador-calendario-adviento.jpg"
      alt="Screenshot of the Alumini ONE winners announcement"
      class="mx-auto my-4 rounded-lg shadow-md"
    />
    <p class="mb-4">
      This recognition was a great incentive and demonstrates the value of
      actively participating in development communities.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <div class="p-0 py-4 sm:p-6 sm:py-0">
      <header class="mb-4 text-center">
        <a
          href="https://xeland314.github.io/advent-calendar/"
          target="_blank"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
        >
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold">
            Advent Calendar Preview
          </h3>
        </a>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-white">Experience how it works!</p>
      </header>
      <div class="relative w-full h-96 border rounded-lg shadow-lg">
        <iframe
          src="https://xeland314.github.io/advent-calendar/"
          title="Advent Calendar Interactive Preview"
          class="w-full h-full rounded-lg border-none"></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Description</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This project is a digital advent calendar developed in Next.js and exported
      as a static page. Each day, users can open a "window" that reveals a
      message or virtual gift. The design is inspired by the holidays, using
      red, green, and gold colors and a festive typography. Additionally, the
      project has a pixel art style.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Details</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        Displays a December calendar with 24 days represented as boxes.
      </li>
      <li>
        Allows users to open a new box only on or after the corresponding day
        (uses the system date).
      </li>
      <li>
        Each box reveals surprise content (message, image, or a festive GIF).
      </li>
      <li>Uses smooth animations when opening the boxes.</li>
      <li>Includes a counter that shows how many days are left until Christmas.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Technologies Used</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong>Next.js</strong>: React framework for creating web applications.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>React</strong>: JavaScript library for building user interfaces.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Tailwind CSS and CSS</strong>: For design and animations.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong
          ><a
            href="https://github.com/aseprite/aseprite"
            class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
          >
            Aseprite:
          </a></strong
        >For the visual style used in the project and images created with a
        pixel art style.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Installation</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-4">
      <li>
        <strong>Clone the repository:</strong>
        <CodeBlock
          code="git clone https://github.com/xeland314/advent-calendar.git"
          client:visible
        />
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Navigate to the project directory:</strong>
        <CodeBlock code="cd advent-calendar" client:visible />
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Install the dependencies:</strong>
        <CodeBlock code="npm install" client:visible />
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Start the development server:</strong>
        <CodeBlock code="npm run dev" client:visible />
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Deployment</h2>
    <p>
      The project is deployed as a static page and can be viewed at the
      following link:
    </p>
    <a
      href="https://xeland314.github.io/advent-calendar/"
      class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
    >
      ðŸ”— Project: Advent Calendar
    </a>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Author</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Christopher VillamarÃ­n</strong> -{" "}
      <a
        href="https://github.com/xeland314"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
      >
        GitHub
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
